nty Public Schools]] |accessdate=2018-11-14}}</ref>\n* The Benjamin Banneker Preparatory Charter School, [[Willingboro, New Jersey]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115005642/https://bannekerprep.com/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=231684&type=d|archivedate=2018-11-15 |url=https://www.bannekerprep.com/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=231684&type=d |title=Mission and Vision|work=The Benjamin Banneker Preparatory Charter School |accessdate=2018-11-15|via=Educational Networks}}</ref>\n\n===Elementary Schools===\n* Banneker Group (23 elementary schools), [[St. Louis, Missouri]]<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wyant|first=Willam K;, Jr.|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uiug.30112004337389;view=1up;seq=59|title=Reading: A Way Upward|work=[[The Saturday Evening Post]]|date=April 16, 1942|quote=The lights of the Carver School were burning for a meeting of parents, faculty members and a team of educators led by Samuel Shepard, Jr., director of the Banneker group of 23 elementary schools.  The Banneker Group is one of five areas into which St. Louis's 150 elementary schools are divided. Covering 15 square miles, it embraces a railroad yard and five low-income public-housing projects.<br />In the Banneker schools, more than 95% of the students are Negroes.}}<br />''In'' {{cite book|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uiug.30112004337389;view=1up;seq=1|title=Civil rights U.S.A.: Public Schools: Cities in the North and West: 1962: St. Louis: A report to the United States Commission on Civil Rights (Appendix E)|page=303|first=Wylie H.|last=Davis|year=1962|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[United States Government Publishing Office|United States Government Printing Office]]|oclc=784219767|accessdate=2019-03-11|via=[[HathiTrust]] Digital Library}}</ref>\n* Banneker-Doyle Career and Transition Center, [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101070349/http://bannekerctc-lausd-ca.schoolloop.com/|archivedate=2018-11-01 |url=http://search.lausd.k12.ca.us/cgi-bin/fccgi.exe?w3exec=find3&which=1941 |title=Banneker Career and Transition Center|location=Los Angeles, California |publisher=[[Los Angeles Unified School District]]|via=SchoolLoop |accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Banneker Elementary School, [[Saint Louis, Virginia|St. Louis]], [[Loudoun County, Virginia]]<ref>(1) {{cite web |last=Smith |first=Ethel |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115010311/https://www.lcps.org/Domain/5757|archivedate=2018-11-15 |url=http://lcps.org//Domain/5757 |title=Early History of Banneker School |work=Banneker Elementary School |publisher=[[Loudoun County Public Schools]] |accessdate=2018-11-15}}<br />(2) {{cite web |url=http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=5200 |title=\"History of St. Louis\" marker |publisher=HMdb.org: The Historical Marker Database |accessdate=2014-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313001100/http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=5200 |archivedate=2014-03-13 |quote=A six room school was built in 1948, and named after Benjamin Banneker, a famous African American scientist, inventor, surveyor & anti slavery publicist.}}</ref>\n* Banneker Elementary Science & Technology Magnet School, [[Kansas City, Kansas]]<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728071956/http://banneker.schools.kckps.org:80/grhuffm/schoolinfo.html|archivedate=2012-07-28 |url=http://banneker.schools.kckps.org/grhuffm/schoolinfo.html |title=School Information |work=Banneker Elementary Science & Technology Magnet School |location=[[Kansas City, Kansas]] |publisher=[[Kansas City, Kansas Public Schools|Kansas City, Kansas, Public Schools]] |accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Academy, [[East Orange, New Jersey]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206172652/http://banneker.eastorange.schoolfusion.us:80/ |archivedate=2017-12-06 |title=Benjamin Banneker Academy |url=http://banneker.eastorange.schoolfusion.us/ |year=2012 |location=[[East Orange, New Jersey]] |publisher=Benjamin Banneker Academy |accessdate=2012-09-05}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Achievement Center, [[Gary, Indiana]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180106193530/http://www.garycsc.k12.in.us:80/schools/benjamin-banneker/ |archivedate=2018-01-06 |url=http://www.garycsc.k12.in.us:80/schools/benjamin-banneker/ |title=Benjamin Banneker Achievement Center |location=[[Gary, Indiana]] |publisher=[[Gary Community School Corporation]] |date=2016-08-23|via=SMDG|accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Charter Academy of Technology, [[Kansas City, Missouri]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115012007/https://www.bbchartertech.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=99451&type=d|archivedate=2018-11-15 |url=http://www.bbchartertech.org/apps/pages/?uREC_ID=99451&type=d |title=Benjamin Banneker Charter Academy of Technology |location=[[Kansas City, Missouri]] |publisher=Benjamin Banneker Charter Academy of Technology |accessdate=2018-11-15 |via=Educational Networks}}</ref>\n[[File:Banneker School, Parkville, MO.jpg|thumb|right|200px|<center>Benjamin Banneker School, Parkville, Missouri (2018)</center>]]\n* Benjamin Banneker Elementary School, Chicago, Illinois<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517052931/http://www.cps.edu/Schools/Pages/school.aspx?id=610265 |archivedate=2013-05-17 |url=http://www.cps.edu/Schools/Pages/school.aspx?id=610265 |title=Banneker |publisher=[[Chicago Public Schools]] |work=Schools |location=Chicago, Illinois |year=2012 |accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Elementary School, Kansas City, Missouri<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926193909/https://www.kcpublicschools.org/domain/212 |archivedate=2018-09-26 |url=https://www.kcpublicschools.org/domain/212|title=About Benjamin Banneker Elementary |work=Benjamin Banneker Elementary |location=[[Kansas City, Missouri]] 