tuyvesant, Brooklyn.}}</ref>\n* [[Benjamin Banneker School]], [[Parkville, Missouri]] (historical)<ref>{{cite web |last=Rau |first=Jean |last2=Fleming |first2=Beverly A. |last3=Mitchell |first3=Steven |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023011232/http://dnr.mo.gov/shpo/nps-nr/95001115.pdf |archivedate=2017-10-23 |url=http://www.dnr.mo.gov/shpo/nps-nr/95001115.pdf |format=PDF |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration Form: Benjamin Banneker School |publisher=[[United States Department of the Interior]]: [[National Park Service]] |accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n\n===Other===\n* Benjamin Banneker Institute, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania (historical)<ref>(1) {{cite web|editor-first=Bill|editor-last=Pfingsten|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403233006/https://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=82535|archivedate=2019-04-03|url=https://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=82535|title=\"Benjamin Banneker Institute\" marker|publisher=HMdb: [[Historical Marker Database|The Historical Marker Database]]|date=2016-06-16|accessdate=2019-04-03|quote=Founded here in 1854 and dedicated to the literary betterment of African Americans, this school was named for a Black astronomer and mathematician who published an almanac and helped survey Washington, D.C.}}<br />(2) {{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404003142/http://explorepahistory.com/story.php?storyId=1-9-21&chapter=3|archivedate=2019-04-04|url=http://explorepahistory.com/story.php?storyId=1-9-21&chapter=3|title=Chapter Three: \"An Open Field and No Favors\": Education and the Quest for Equality|work=\"The Surest Foundation of Happiness\": Education in Pennsylvania|publisher=ExplorePAHistory.com: Stories from PA History|year=2011|accessdate=2019-04-04|quote=Inspired by the growing agitation over slavery and racial inequality, Pennsylvania abolitionists founded other schools for black Pennsylvanians. Some, including Avery College in Pittsburgh (1849) and the Benjamin Banneker Institute in Philadelphia (1854), were short-lived.}}<br />(3) {{cite web|url=http://www.preservationalliance.com/inventory-african-american-historic-sites/|title=Benjamin Banneker Institute|work=Inventory of African American Historic Sites|year=2015|location=Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|publisher=Preservation Alliance for Greater Philadelphia.}}</ref>\n\n==Professorships and scholarships==\nThe names of several university professorships and scholarships commemorate Banneker. These include:\n* Benjamin Banneker Professorship of American Studies and History, [[Columbian College of Arts and Sciences]], [[George Washington University]], Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106184729/https://americanstudies.columbian.gwu.edu/james-oliver-horton|archivedate=2018-11-06|url=http://departments.columbian.gwu.edu/americanstudies/people/162 |title=James Oliver Horton: Benjamin Banneker Professor Emeritus of American Studies and History |work=Columbian College of Arts and Sciences: The Department of American Studies |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=[[George Washington University]] |accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Scholarship Program, Central State University, Wilberforce, Ohio<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090315205635/http://www.centralstate.edu/academics/support/cso/scholarships/pdf/Banneker-NSF%20Scholarship%20Packet08.pdf |archivedate=2009-03-15 |url=http://www.centralstate.edu/academics/support/cso/scholarships/pdf/Banneker-NSF%20Scholarship%20Packet08.pdf |format=PDF |title=The National Science Foundation Benjamin Banneker Scholarship Program, Central State University |work=Center for Student Opportunities Scholarship Programs |location=[[Wilberforce, Ohio]] |publisher=[[Central State University]] |accessdate=2012-09-14}}</ref>\n*Banneker/Key Scholarship, [[University of Maryland Honors College]], [[College Park, Maryland]]<ref>(1) {{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428115058/http://www.bannekerkey.umd.edu/|archivedate=2018-04-28 |url=http://www.bannekerkey.umd.edu/ |title=Banneker/Key Scholars |location=[[College Park, Maryland]] |publisher=[[University of Maryland Honors College]] |accessdate=2018-11-15}}<br />(2) {{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130063234/https://law.resource.org/pub/us/case/reporter/F3/038/38.F3d.147.93-2585.93-2527.html |archivedate=2016-01-30 |url=https://law.resource.org/pub/us/case/reporter/F3/038/38.F3d.147.93-2585.93-2527.html |title=Podberesky v. Kirwin, 38 F.3d 147 (4th Cir. 1994): 63 USLW 2287, 95 Ed. Law Rep. 52 |work=[[United States courts of appeals|United States Court of Appeals]], Fourth Circuit |date=1994-10-27 |publisher=Public.Resource.org |accessdate=2016-01-30 |quote=The issue in this case is whether the University of Maryland at College Park may maintain a separate merit scholarship program that it voluntarily established for which only African-American students are eligible. Because we find that the district court erred in finding that the University had sufficient evidence of present effects of past discrimination to justify the program and in finding that the program is narrowly tailored to serve its stated objectives, we reverse the district court's grant of summary judgment to the University. We further reverse the district court's denial of Podberesky's motion for summary judgment, and we remand for entry of judgment in favor of Podberesky.<br />The facts and prior proceedings in this case are set forth at length in our earlier opinion, Podberesky v. Kirwan, 956 F.2d 52 (4th Cir.1992) (Podberesky I). In sum, Daniel Podberesky challenges the University of Maryland's Banneker scholarship program, which is a merit-based program for which only African-American students are eligible. The University maintains a separate merit-based scholarship program, the Francis Scott Key program, which is not restricted to African-American students. Podberesky is Hispanic; he was therefore ineligible for consideration under the Banneker Program, although he met the academic and all other requirements for consideration. Podberesky was ineligible for consideration under the Key program because his academic credentials fell just shy of its more rigorous standards. ....}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nThe names of several awards commemorate Banneker. These include:\n* Benjamin Banneker Award, [[Alabama Agricultural and Mechanical University]], [[Huntsville, Alabama]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203192640/http://www.aamu.edu/news/Lists/Events/DispForm.aspx?ID=483|archivedate=2016-02-03 |url=http://www.aamu.edu/news/Lists/Events/DispForm.aspx?ID=483 |title=Benjamin Banneker Awards Banquet |date=2012-02-27 |location=[[Huntsville, Alabama]] |publisher=[[Alabama Agricultural and Mechanical University]] |accessdate=2012-10-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Award, [[Temple University]] [[School of education|College of Education]], Philadelphia, Pennsylvania<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330235724/http://www.temple.edu/education/graduation/awards.html |archivedate=2009-03-30 |url=http://www.temple.edu/education/graduation/awards.html |title=Benjamin Banneker Award |work=College of Education Commencement Awards |location=[[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania |publisher=[[Temple University]] |year=2004 |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=Benjamin Banneker Award) The purpose of the FUND is to provide an annual award for a full-time graduate student in the College of Education who worked as a research or teaching assistant in the College during the academic year prior to receiving the award, and who showed outstanding work and initiative in carrying out his or her research/teaching activities.}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Award for Excellence in Math and Science, Metropolitan Buffalo Alliance of Black School Educators, [[Buffalo, New York]]<ref>(1) {{cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116022035/https://buffalonews.com/2004/11/05/buffalos-high-scoring-students-honored-for-academic-achievement/|archivedate=2018-11-16|url=https://buffalonews.com/2004/11/05/buffalos-high-scoring-students-honored-for-academic-achievement/|author=Staff|title=Buffalo's High-Scoring Students Honored for Academic Achievement|work=[[The Buffalo News]]|location=[[Buffalo, New York]]|date=2004-11-06|accessdate=2018-11-16|quote=From a fifth-grader to several high school seniors, 12 Buffalo students will be honored this weekend at the third annual Benjamin Banneker Awards of Excellence in Math and Science.}}<br />(2) {{cite web|url=https://www.buffaloshools.org/Page/63752 |title=7th Annual Benjamin Banneker Award of Excellence in Math and Science|work=Awards|publisher=PS 192: Buffalo Academy for Visual and Performing Arts|location=[[Buffalo, New York]]|year=2018|via=Blackboard|accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Award for Outstanding Social Commitment and Community Initiatives, [[American Planning Association]], [[Washington Metropolitan Area|National Capital Area]] Chapter, Washington, D.C.<ref>(1) {{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218035231/https://yippsdc.wordpress.com/page/2/?archives-list=1 |archivedate=2017-02-18 |url=https://yippsdc.wordpress.com/page/2/?archives-list=1 |title=Benjamin Banneker Award for Outstanding Social Commitment and Community Initiatives: |work=APA NCAC Awards Nominations Now Open: National Capital Area Chapter \u2013 APA Now Accepting Planning Award Nominations!: National Capital Area Chapter of the [[American Planning Association]] |publisher=YIPPS: Young, Innovative, Professional Planning Superstars in Washington DC |date=2010-09-09 |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=This award honors a group, individual, or initiative that has developed initiatives and/or demonstrated a sustained commitment to reach beyond and expand the traditional scope of planning, particularly to advance social objectives. This could include efforts such as community policing or drug prevention, neighborhood outreach initiatives, programs designed for diverse populations, public art or cultural efforts, community festivals, environmental conservation initiatives, summer recreational initiatives for children, or community food production.}}<br />(2) {{cite web|author=National Capital Area Chapter of the [[American Planning Association]]|url=https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5612e13ae4b0c37386e86b7e/t/5a5f59c20d92977380e4d4f2/1516198339211/2012.jpg|title=2012 Benjamin Banneker Award for Outstanding Social Commitment and Community Initiatives|date=2012-11-10|accessdate=2019-03-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190314145113/https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5612e13ae4b0c37386e86b7e/t/5a5f59c20d92977380e4d4f2/1516198339211/2012.jpg|archivedate=2019-03-14}}\n</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Legacy Award, The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science and Technology, Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304003942/http://www.thebannekerinstitute.org/events/benjamin-banneker-legacy-award-winners |archivedate=2016-03-04 |url=http://www.thebannekerinstitute.org/events/benjamin-banneker-legacy-award-winners |title=Benjamin Banneker Legacy Award Winners: 2006 Award Winners |year=2006 |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science and Technology |accessdate=2017-02-17}}</ref>\n\n==Streets==\nThe names of a number of streets throughout the United States commemorate Banneker. These include:\n* Banneker Avenue, [[Richmond Heights, Missouri]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Avenue, [[Richmond Heights, Missouri]]: {{coord|38.6243918|-90.33350|type:landmark|name=Banneker Avenue, Richmond Heights, Missouri|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Avenue North, [[Minneapolis]], Minnesota<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Avenue North, [[Minneapolis]], Minnesota: {{coord|44.9899561|-93.2975766|type:landmark|name=Banneker Avenue North, Minneapolis, Minnesota}}</ref>\n* Banneker Court, Detroit, Michigan<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Court, Detroit, Michigan: {{coord|42.3910148|-82.974933|type:landmark|name=Banneker Court, Detroit, Michigan|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Court, [[Mobile, Alabama]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Court, [[Mobile, Alabama]]: {{coord|30.7181507|-88.0940791|type:landmark|name=Banneker Court, Mobile, Alabama|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Court, [[Stone Mountain, Georgia]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Court, [[Stone Mountain, Georgia]]: {{coord|33.836538|-84.1828309|type:landmark|name=Banneker Court, Stone Mountain, Georgia|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Court, [[Wilmington, Delaware]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Court, [[Wilmington, Delaware]]: {{coord|39.7243704|-75.5459409|type:landmark|name=Banneker Court, Wilmington, Delaware|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Cove, [[Memphis, Tennessee]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Cove, [[Memphis, Tennessee]]: {{coord|35.0041318|-90.0717804|type:landmark|name=Banneker Cove, Memphis, Tennessee|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Drive, San Diego<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Drive, San Diego: {{coord|32.7125172|-117.0328774|type:landmark|name=Banneker Drive, San Diego, California|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Drive, [[Williamsburg, Virginia]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Drive, [[Williamsburg, Virginia]]: {{coord|37.2495039|-76.6572029|type:landmark|name=Banneker Drive, Williamsburg, Virginia|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Drive [[Northeast, Washington, D.C.]]<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Drive Northeast, Washington, D.C.: {{coord|38.9259512|-76.9615853|type:landmark|name=Banneker Drive Northeast, Washington, D.C.|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Lane, Annapolis, Maryland<ref group=\"a\">Coordinates of Banneker Lane, [[Annapolis, Maryland]]: {{coord|38.9653623|-76.5314086|type:landmark|name=Banneker Lane, Annapolis, Maryland|format=dms}}</ref>\n* Banneker Place, [[