lumbia-MD/7699282/|title=Banneker Building |publisher=[[LoopNet]] |accessdate=2012-09-19}}</ref>\n* Banneker Gardens, [[Cumberland, Maryland]] (townhomes/apartments)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023011236/http://cumberlandhousing.org/content/banneker_gardens|archivedate=2017-10-23 |url=http://cumberlandhousing.org/content/banneker_gardens |title=Banneker Gardens |work=Cumberland Housing |location=[[Cumberland, Maryland]] |publisher=Cumberland Housing Alliance |accessdate=2012-09-13}}</ref>\n* Banneker Homes, San Francisco<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804202426/http://bannekerhomes.com/ |archivedate=2018-08-04 |url=http://bannekerhomes.com/|title=Banneker Homes|publisher=Banneker Homes |year=2016 |accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Banneker Place, [[Town Center, Columbia, Maryland]]<ref name=\"Town Center Community Association\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425073640/http://towncenter.columbiavillages.org:80/files/Know_Your_Village_Neighborhoods_11-7-11.pdf |archivedate=2012-04-25|url=http://towncenter.columbiavillages.org/files/Know_Your_Village_Neighborhoods_11-7-11.pdf |format=PDF |title=Know Your Neighborhoods: Town Center |location=[[Columbia, Maryland]] |publisher=Town Center Community Association |accessdate=2012-09-12|quote=<br />What Neighborhood Is Your Development In?<br />.........<br />Banneker<br />Banneker Place}}</ref>\n* Banneker Place apartments, Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328171414/http://www.apartmentshowcase.com:80/details/district-of-columbia/washington/banneker-place/3019|archivedate=2017-03-28 |url=http://www.apartmentshowcase.com:80/details/district-of-columbia/washington/banneker-place/3019|title=Banneker Place in Washington, D.C. |work=Apartment Showcase |publisher=The Washington Post |year=2012 |accessdate=2012-09-11}}</ref>\n\n==Businesses==\nThe names of a number of businesses commemorate Banneker. These include:\n* Banneker Energy, LLC, [[Duluth, Georgia]] and New Orleans, Louisiana (transportation fuel management)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023063111/http://bannekerenergy.com/index.html |archivedate=2017-10-23 |url=http://bannekerenergy.com/index.html |title=Banneker Energy, LLC |location=[[Duluth, Georgia]] |publisher=Banneker Energy, LLC |accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>\n* Banneker, Inc., [[Denver]], Colorado (watches and clocks)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618134538/http://www.bannekerstore.com/banneker-company |archivedate=2016-06-18 |url=http://www.bannekerstore.com/about-us |title=Our Company |work=Bannekerstore.com |location=Denver, Colorado |publisher=Banneker, Inc: Benjamin Banneker Watches and Clocks |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=The watch and clock offerings of the company are differentiated in the marketplace by virtue of a unique design feature that connects us to our legendary namesake. Benjamin Banneker (1731-1806) was a free African American astronomer, inventor, mathematician, surveyor, almanac author, and farmer. The historic contribution that aligns us with this man of genius is outlined below. ....}}</ref> \n* Banneker Industries, Inc., [[North Smithfield, Rhode Island]] (supply chain management)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.banneker.com/about-us/company-overview/ |title=Company Overview |work=Banneker: World Class Supply Chain Solutions |location=[[North Smithfield, Rhode Island]] |publisher=Banneker Industries, Inc. |year=2012 |accessdate=2012-09-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130211084709/http://www.banneker.com/about-us/company-overview/ |archivedate=2013-02-11 |quote=Banneker Industries is named after Benjamin Banneker (1731-1806), the first recognized African American mathematician, astronomer and inventor. He is credited with making the first American striking clock, publishing several almanacs and was influential in the design of our nation\u2019s capitol.}}</ref>\n* Banneker Ventures, LLC, Washington, D.C. and [[Rockville, Maryland]] (design, construction and contracting management)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120913073651/http://bannekerventures.com/about_overview.html |archivedate=2012-09-13 |url=http://bannekerventures.com/about_overview.html |title=About Us |work=Banneker Ventures |location=Washington, D.C. and Rockville, Maryland |publisher=Banneker Ventures, LLC |year=2011 |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=The firm is named in honor of the brilliant mathematician, astronomer and surveyor Benjamin Banneker who worked on the survey for the Federal District, which is now Washington, D.C. Born in 1731, Benjamin Banneker lived a life of unusual achievement. He was an astronomer, predicting future solar and lunar eclipses, compiling the ephemeris for annual almanacs which became top sellers in the Mid-Atlantic region of the United States, mathematician, and surveyor. In 1980, the U.S. Postal Service issued a postage stamp in his honor.}}</ref>\n* The Banneker Group, LLC, [[Laurel, Maryland]] (general contracting and facility maintenance)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130428084830/http://www.thebannekergroup.com/about.asp |archivedate=2013-04-28 |url=http://www.thebannekergroup.com/about.asp |title=The Banneker Group, LLC: General Contracting and Facility Maintenance |location=Laurel, Maryland |publisher=The Banneker Group |year=2013 |accessdate=2017-02-18}}</ref>\n\n==Advocacy groups==\nThe names and/or goals of several advocacy groups commemorate Banneker. These include:\n* The Benjamin Banneker Association, Inc. (BANNEKERMATH.org), [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219074425/http://bannekermath.org/about-bba/|archivedate=2014-12-19 |url=http://bannekermath.org/about-bba/ |title=About BBA |work=BANNEKERMATH.org: The Benjamin Banneker Association |location=[[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania |publisher=BANNEKERMATH.org |year=2012 |accessdate=2012-09-11 |quote=The Benjamin Banneker Association, Inc. is a national non-profit organization dedicated to mathematics education advocacy, establishing a presence for leadership, and professional development to support teachers in leveling the playing field for mathematics learning of the highest quality for African-American students.}}</ref>\n* The Benjamin Banneker Center for Economic Justice and Progress, Baltimore, Maryland<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908113704/http://www.progress.org/banneker/index.shtml |archivedate=2014-09-08 |url=http://www.progress.org/banneker/index.shtm|title=The Benjamin Banneker Center for Economic Justice |location=Baltimore, Maryland |publisher=The Benjamin Banneker Center for Economic Justice and Progress |accessdate=2012-12-09}}</ref>\n* The Benjamin Banneker Foundation, [[Fulton, Maryland]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bannekerfoundation.com/about_us |title=About The Foundation |work=Benjamin Banneker Foundation |date=2016-12-27 |location=[[Fulton, Maryland]] |publisher=Benjamin Banneker Foundation, Inc. |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=The Benjamin Banneker Foundation is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit philanthropic group, specializing in fundraising for the Benjamin Banneker Historical Park and Museum. Funds are used to increase educational activities, enhance conservation initiatives, and further develop the Park and Museum into a living history center. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218143552/https://www.bannekerfoundation.com/about_us |archivedate=2017-02-18 }}</ref>\n* The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science & Technology, Washington, D.C.<ref>(1) {{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324130007/http://www.thebannekerinstitute.org/about-us |archivedate=2016-03-24 |url=http://www.thebannekerinstitute.org/about-us |title=The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science and Technology |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science and Technology |year=2000\u20132012 |accessdate=2012-09-10}}<br />(2) {{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215040449/http://catalystdc.org/cpe_the_banneker.htm |archivedate=2017-02-15 |url=http://catalystdc.org/cpe_the_banneker.htm |title=The Benjamin Banneker Institute for Science and Technology |work=Current Projects: Educational Institution Development and Reform |publisher=Catalyst Institute for Applied Policy |year=2007 |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=The mission of the Banneker Institute is to increase access to, and participation and performance in science and math related professions and academic pursuits by African Americans. The Institute proposes to enable more rapid identification and implementation of success models by serving as an information clearinghouse for monitoring the state of the art, identifying best practices, creating opportunities for collaboration, funding and otherwise promoting pilot projects, and granting an annual Banneker Award to honor the contributions of those making significant progress in support of the Institute\u2019s mission.}}</ref>\n* Washington Interdependence Council: Administrators of the Benjamin Banneker Memorial and Banneker Institute of Math & Science, Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129140117/http://www.bannekermemorial.org/aboutus.htm |archivedate=2017-01-29 |url=http://www.bannekermemorial.org/aboutus.htm |title=About Us |work=Washington Interdependence Council: Administrators of the Benjamin Banneker Memorial and Banneker Institute of Math & Science |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=Washington Interdependence Council |year=2016 |accessdate=2017-02-17 |quote=The Washington Interdependence Council (WIC) is a 501(c)3 non-profit civic organization authorized by Congress [P.L. 105-355] to erect a monument to colonial American hero Benjamin Banneker [1731-1806] .}}</ref>\n\n==Other==\n[[File:\"Benjamin Banneker- Surveyor-Inventor-Astronomer,\" mural by Maxime Seelbinder, at the Recorder of Deeds building, built in 1943. 515 D St., NW, Washington, D.C LCCN2010641717.tif|thumb|right|200px|<center><sup>[[Library of Congress]]</sup></center>Benjamin Banneker mural in the Recorder of Deeds building in Washington, D.C.<ref name=Seelbinder/>]]\nOther commemorations of Benjamin Banneker include:\n* \"Banneker\",<ref>(1) {{cite web|last=Dove|first=Rita|authorlink=Rita Dove|url=http://www.poetryfoundation.org/poem/172127|work=Poems & Poets |title=Banneker|publisher=[[Poetry Foundation]]|year=1983|accessdate=February 20, 2018}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220134254/https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poems/43354/banneker|date=February 20, 2018}}<br>(2) {{cite web|first=Amanda|last=Newton|url=http://ritadoveatwandl.blogspot.com/2012/03/analysis-on-banneker-and-parsley.html|title=Analysis on \"Banneker\" and \"Parsley\"|work=Spotlight on Rita Dove|date=2012-03-04|publisher=[[Blogger (service)|Blogger]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220141926/http://ritadoveatwandl.blogspot.com/2012/03/analysis-on-banneker-and-parsley.html|date=February 20, 2018}}</ref> a 1983 poem by [[Rita Dove]] (1993-1995 [[United States Poet Laureate]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Comprehensive Biography of Rita Dove|url=http://people.virginia.edu/~rfd4b/compbio.html|work=The Rita Dove Home Page|publisher=[[University of Virginia]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220152646/http://people.virginia.edu/~rfd4b/compbio.html|date=February 20, 2018}}</ref>\n* Banneker City Little League, Washington, D.C. (youth baseball)<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831112328/http://bannekercityll.org/|url=http://bannekercityll.org/ |archivedate=2018-08-31|title=Banneker City Little League |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=Banneker City Baseball |year=2018 |accessdate=2018-11-15}}</ref>\n* Banneker Institute, [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]] (summer program in astronomy)<ref name=Institute>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120062215/https://bannekerinstitute.fas.harvard.edu/|archivedate=2019-01-20|url=https://bannekerinstitute.fas.harvard.edu|title=Banneker Institute|work=[[Harvard University]]|year=2019|location=[[Cambridge, Massachusetts]]|publisher=[[President and Fellows of Harvard College|The President and Fellows of Harvard College]]|accessdate=2019-03-31|quote=The Banneker Institute summer program is a full-time, ten-week research and study experience. We prepare undergraduate students of color for graduate programs in astronomy by emphasizing research, building community, and encouraging debate and political action through social justice education.}}</ref>\n* Banneker Literary Institute, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania (historical)<ref>(1) {{cite web |first=Aslaku |last=Berhanu |url=http://stillfamily.library.temple.edu/people-and-places/benjamin-banneker-institute |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141126024455/http://stillfamily.library.temple.edu/people-and-places/benjamin-banneker-institute |archivedate=2014-11-26 |title=Benjamin Banneker Institute |work=William Still: An African-American Abolitionist |publisher=University Libraries: [[Temple University]] |location=Philadelphia, Pennsylvania |accessdate=2017-02-19 |quote=The Banneker Literary Institute, named after black mathematician Benjamin Banneker, was one of several literary and debating societies in nineteenth-century Philadelphia. Organized in 1854 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania by a group of prominent men, the Banneker Institute promoted literary and other intellectual endeavors. ..... The Banneker Institute was the forerunner of the Afro-American Historical Society, which was established in 1879.}}<br>(2) {{cite journal |last=Lapsansky |first=Emma Jones (January/April 1993) |jstor=20092777|title=\u2019Discipline to the Mind\u2019: Philadelphia\u2019s Banneker Institute, 1854-1872 |journal=The Pennsylvania Magazine of History and Biography |volume=117 |number=1/2 |pages=83\u2013102 |publisher=[[Historical Society of Pennsylvania]]|via=[[JSTOR]]}}.</ref> \n* Banneker neighborhood, Town Center, Columbia, Maryland<ref name=\"Town Center Community Association\"/>\n* Benjamin Banneker Honors Math & Science Society, [[Washington Metropolitan Area]]: Washington, D.C., Virginia and Maryland<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625061452/http://www.bbhmss.org/ |archivedate=2011-06-25 |url=http://www.bbhmss.org/ |title=Benjamin Banneker Honors Math & Science Society |date=2012-10-22 |accessdate=2012-10-18 |quote=Mission - The Benjamin Banneker Honors Math and Science Society (BBHMSS) is an organization whose mission is to improve minority students academic standing with respect to mathematics and science.}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker Mathematics Competition, [[Pittsburgh]], Pennsylvania<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023012155/http://www.ntaonline.org/pittsburgh.html|archivedate=2017-10-23 |url=http://www.ntaonline.org/pittsburgh.html |title=NTA Pittsburgh Chapter: History |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=National Technical Association, Inc. |year=2012 |accessdate=2018-11-15 |quote=The primary goals of the NTA are:<br />To encourage minority youth to pursue careers in technical areas which will enable them to become successful doctors, scientists and other technical professionals.<br>To aid in the professional development of its members.<br />To provide an outlet for minority technical professionals to broaden its network.<br />These goals were accomplished through several programs serving students in grades 3 through 12 in the Pittsburgh Public Schools, such as the Benjamin Banneker Mathematics Competition, the Charles Drew Science Fair and the Elementary Science Program.}}</ref>\n* Benjamin Banneker mural, Recorder of Deeds Building, Washington, D.C.<ref name=Seelbinder>(1) {{cite web |last=Highsmith|first=Carol M. (photographer)|authorlink=Carol M. Highsmith|url=http://loc.gov/pictures/resource/highsm.09905/| format=photograph|title=\"Benjamin Banneker: Surveyor-Inventor-Astronomer,\" mural by Maxime Seelbinder, at the Recorder of Deeds building, built in 1943. 515 D St., NW, Washington, D.C.|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[Library of Congress]]|accessdate=November 5, 2017}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171101123251/http://www.loc.gov/pictures/resource/highsm.09905/|date=2017-11-01}}<br>(2) {{cite web|url=https://livingnewdeal.org/projects/recorder-deeds-building-seelbinder-mural-washington-dc/ |title=Recorder of Deeds Building: Seelbinder Mural \u2013 Washington DC |publisher=The Living New Deal|accessdate=January 11, 2020}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111054138/https://livingnewdeal.org/projects/recorder-deeds-building-seelbinder-mural-washington-dc/|date=January 11, 2020}}<br>(3) {{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/03/09/AR2010030903458.html |title=D.C. Recorder of Deeds moving but fate of murals unclear |first=Nicole |last=Norfleet|date=March 11, 2010|work=The Breaking News Blog |publisher=[[The Washington Post]] |location=Washington, D.C.|accessdate=October 3, 2016}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003210410/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/03/09/AR2010030903458.html|date=October 3, 2016}}</ref> \n* Benjamin Banneker obelisk, [[Mount Gilboa Chapel]], Oella, Maryland (see: [[Mount Gilboa Chapel]]).<ref>(1) [http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=5859 \"Benjamin Banneker\" marker] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111019195152/http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=5859 |date=2011-10-19 }} ''in'' HMdb.org: [[Historical Marker Database|The Historical Marker Database]]] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110303154048/http://www.hmdb.org/ |date=2011-03-03 }}. Retrieved 2008-08-27.<br>