.org/html/articles/theosophy/bevir3.html Annie Besant's Quest for Truth: Christianity, Secularism, and New Age Thought]\n*[http://www.victorianweb.org/authors/besant/diniejko.html Annie Besant's Multifaceted Personality. A Biographical Sketch]\n*[http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39076005046201;view=1up;seq=9 Thought power, its control and culture] Cornell University Library Historical Monographs Collection.\n*[http://www.freemasonryformenandwomen.co.uk The British Federation of the International Order of Co-Freemasonry, Le Droit Humain, founded by Annie Besant in 1902]\n*[http://www.varanasi.org.in/annie-besant Annie Besant] Biography at [http://www.varanasi.org.in varanasi.org.in]\n*[[William Thomas Stead]], [http://www.attackingthedevil.co.uk/reviews/besant.php \u201cCharacter Sketch: October of Mrs. Annie Besant\u201d 349\u2013367 in ''Review of Reviews'' IV:22, October 1891.]\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/001635}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{Succession box| title = [[President of the Indian National Congress]] | years = 1917 |before = [[Ambica Charan Mazumdar]]| after = [[Madan Mohan Malaviya]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Indian National Congress Presidents}}\n{{Indian independence movement}}\n{{Theosophy series}}\n{{Modern Hindu writers}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Besant, Annie}}\n[[Category:1847 births]]\n[[Category:1933 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Clapham]]\n[[Category:Theosophy]]\n[[Category:English Theosophists]]\n[[Category:Esoteric Christianity]]\n[[Category:British birth control activists]]\n[[Category:English occult writers]]\n[[Category:English non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:English spiritual writers]]\n[[Category:English activists]]\n[[Category:English women activists]]\n[[Category:English socialists]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Indian National Congress]]\n[[Category:English suffragists]]\n[[Category:Feminist writers]]\n[[Category:History of Chennai]]\n[[Category:English women writers]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Birkbeck, University of London]]\